@model Farkle.Views.Home.RulesModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Rules";
}
<div class="rules-page">

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
    <p>
        Each player takes their turn rolling all six dice and uses the scoring chart to see if they have any matching
        combinations. Any die or dice that score points may be set aside and that player may choose to roll their remaining
        dice again. The player must set aside at least one scoring die but it is not required to set aside all scoring dice.
        Any dice that are not set aside may be rolled again. If all six dice are set aside, the player can choose to roll
        all six dice again and continue adding to their turns score or they can bank all their points and end their turn.
        A players turn ends when they decide to bank after setting aside or until they fail to roll any scoring dice.
        When a player rolls no scoring dice, they committed farkle. If a player farkles, they lose all points set aside during that turn
        and their turn automatically ends. At the end of a players turn, their points set aside are banked and kept in their total score which
        cannot be lost. 
    </p>
